Torino wing-back, Ola Aina, has been forced to withdraw from Nigeria’s squad to face Brazil in an international friendly fixture on Sunday afternoon in Singapore due to injury. Aina, a former Chelsea star, was involved in a domestic accident. The Nigeria Football Federation (NFF) made this known in a tweet on their official Twitter page on Wednesday. “Just in: Torino of Italy wing-back Ola Aina is out of Sunday’s international friendly against Brazil,” NFF tweeted. “He picked up an injury after a domestic accident and will not be available. #SoarSuperEagles #Team9jaStrong.” Nigeria head to the game following a 2-2 draw with Ukraine in their last friendly game. The kick-off time for the match is 1pm. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.